description.narrative: Youth-friendly health and socio-pedagogical services are better oriented towards vulnerable adolescents, have greater outreach and cover mental health issues, which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Adolescent Health And Nutrition (Covid), Evaluation And Research, Hiv Prevention, Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas, Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas (Covid), Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Supply And Logistics, Supply And Logistics (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2025, children, adolescents and youth are better protected more socially included, prepared for the employment challenges of the future, and engaged in issues of their concern
